TILA - WMS-C and Google Maps Tile Cache Server
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------
Jose Luis Martin - Jun 2012

Tila (TIles on LAn) is a tile cache server for WMS-C and Google Maps. 
Tila will solve performance problems in applications using a map tile server 
by storing tiles on your LAN.

Tila is still on development but downloable versions are usable.

For version 0.0.2 Tila support the folowing caches:

 - GoogleMaps 
 - Open Street Map
 - TMS
 - WMS (Experimental)
 - WTMS 
 
 INSTALL:
 -------------------------------------------------------------------------------- 
 
Download de latest zip file from the download area and deploy tila-version.war it 
on your application server. I'm only tested it on Tomcat 6. 

Then  copy derby database to some path on server and edit the file 
tomcat_root/webapps/tila-version/WEB-INF/jdbc.properties and change the value of
*path_to_db_directory* in property:
 
jdbc.url = "jdbc:derby:/path_to_db_directory"

Restart application and go to http://yourserver:8080/tila/admin to start the admin application 
and set up the tile caches, proxy configuration and cache path in server filesystem.


Tila is open source licensed under Apache Software Foundation 2.0 License.

